						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone lying in front of the Veṅkaṭēśa Bank.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 859-60.</p>						

						<p>This inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 781,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 859-60,</hi> records the grant of land made to <hi rend="bold">Nāguḷa-Basadi,</hi> constructed by <hi rend="bold">Nāguḷara Pollabbe.</hi> The gift was made in the presence of the <hi rend="italic">Ūrgāmuṇḍas.</hi> The recipient of the gift was <hi rend="bold">Nāgaṇandyāchārya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Siṁghavura</hi>-<hi rend="italic">gaṇa.</hi> The village <hi rend="bold">Attīgēri</hi> is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
